Step-by-step explanation:

1. Free Cash Flow (FCF):
 • FCF is calculated as the sum of net cash flow from operating activities and net cash flow from investing activities.
 • In this case: Operating CF = –16,772,398.72 and Investing CF = –2,729,032.26.
 • FCF = –16,772,398.72 + (–2,729,032.26) = –19,401,430.98.

2. Return on Assets (ROA):
 • ROA = (Net Profit) / (End Total Assets). 
 • Net Profit = 1,938,987.47 and Total Assets = 33,082,821.36.
 • ROA = 1,938,987.47 / 33,082,821.36 ≈ 0.05863, or 5.87%.

3. Return on Equity (ROE):
 • ROE = (Net Profit) / (Total Owner's Equity).
 • Total Owner's Equity = 29,938,987.47.
 • ROE = 1,938,987.47 / 29,938,987.47 ≈ 0.06477, or 6.48%.

4. Net Cash Ratio:
 • Here it is defined as the ratio of net cash flow from operating activities to net profit.
 • Ratio = –16,772,398.72 / 1,938,987.47 ≈ –8.65.

5. Net Profit Margin:
 • Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit) / (Total Revenue).
 • Total Revenue = 22,876,677.56.
 • Net Profit Margin = 1,938,987.47 / 22,876,677.56 ≈ 0.0847, or 8.47%.

6. Gross Profit Margin:
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit) / (Total Revenue).
 • Gross Profit = 6,476,677.56.
 • Gross Profit Margin = 6,476,677.56 / 22,876,677.56 ≈ 0.2833, or 28.33%.
